def plot_pscs_t_on_fly(ntor=None, itime=None, savefig=None, outline_eq=False, all_modes=False):
    if ntor not in orbp.n_mode_numbers_nft:
        return
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(**sub_kwargs)
    if all_modes:
        ntitle="all"
        nlist = orbp.n_mode_numbers_nft
    else:
        ntitle=str(ntor)
        nlist = [ntor]
    psc_arr = np.real(orbp.create_potsc(itime, nchi=None, nlist=nlist))
    _ = orbp.plot_psc(psc_arr, fig=fig, ax=ax, aspect=1, cmap='RdBu_r', sym_clim=True, outline=True, outline_eq=outline_eq)
#    ntitle = str(ntor) if ntor != -1 else "all"
    ax.set_title('n={}, t={}'.format(ntitle, orbp.p3t[itime]))
    if savefig:
        fig_filename='psc_n{}_at_t{}.png'.format(ntitle, orbp.p3t[itime])
        fig.savefig(fig_filename)
        print("fig saved to {}".format(fig_filename))
    return fig, ax
fig, ax = plot_pscs_t_on_fly(ntor=26, itime=-1, outline_eq=True)

def plot_m_of_n_at_t(ntor=None, imode=None, itime=None, time=1E6, savefig=False, full_range=True):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    if itime is None:
        itime = np.argmin(np.abs(orbp.p3t[:] - time))
    if imode is None:
        imode, = np.arange(len(orbp.n_mode_numbers))[np.array(orbp.n_mode_numbers)==ntor]
    if full_range:
        mmin = orbp.mharms[imode].min()
        mmax = orbp.mharms[imode].max()
    else:
        mmin = ntor - mlsb
        mmax = ntor + musb
    for iharm, mharm in enumerate(np.arange(mmin, mmax+1)):
        harm = np.sum(orbp.p3dz[itime,imode]*(orbp.mharms[imode]==mharm), axis=1)
        ax.plot(np.abs(harm), label=mharm)
    ax.legend(loc='best', framealpha=0.5, ncol=2)
    ax.set_title("t={}".format(orbp.p3t[itime]))
    if savefig:
        fig.savefig('mharms_in{}_it{}.pdf'.format(imode, itime))
        
nrange=(min(orbp.n_mode_numbers),max(orbp.n_mode_numbers),orbp.nft)
itrange=widgets.IntSlider(min=0, max=orbp.p3t.shape[0]-1, value=orbp.p3t.shape[0]-1, continuous_update=False)

def plot_m_of_n_at_t_jup(ntor=None, itime=None, savefig=False, full_range=False):
    return plot_m_of_n_at_t(ntor=ntor, itime=itime, savefig=savefig, full_range=full_range)

nrange=(min(orbp.n_mode_numbers),max(orbp.n_mode_numbers),orbp.nft)
mrange=widgets.IntSlider(min=0,max=100,value=25)
@interact_manual(mharm=mrange, ntor=nrange, imode=fixed(None))
def m_s_of_t(mharm=-1, imode=None, ntor=None):
    if imode is None:
        imode, = np.arange(len(orbp.n_mode_numbers))[np.array(orbp.n_mode_numbers)==ntor]
    mamp = np.zeros((orbp.p3t.shape[0], orbp.ns_), dtype=np.complex64)
    tmp = orbp.mharms[imode]
    if mharm > tmp.min() and mharm < tmp.max():
        for itime, time in enumerate(orbp.p3t[:]):
            mamp[itime,:] = np.sum(orbp.p3dz[itime,imode]*(tmp==mharm), axis=1)
    st_grid = np.meshgrid(np.arange(orbp.ns_), orbp.p3t[:])
    im = plt.pcolormesh(st_grid[0], st_grid[1], np.real(mamp), cmap='RdBu_r')
    im.set_clim(np.array([-1,1])*np.max(np.abs(im.get_clim())))

#@interact(imode=fixed(None), ntor=nrange, itime=itrange, qband=True)
def plot_dense(imode=None, ntor=None, itime=-1, qband=True):
    if imode is None:
        imode, = np.arange(len(orbp.n_mode_numbers))[np.array(orbp.n_mode_numbers)==ntor]
    ntor = orbp.n_mode_numbers[imode]
    tmp = orbp.mharms[imode]
    dense_mmesh = np.meshgrid(np.arange(tmp.shape[0]), np.arange(tmp.max()+1))
    dense_p3dz_t1 = np.zeros(dense_mmesh[0].shape, dtype=np.complex64)
    p3m = orbp.p3m

    mwidth = tmp.shape[1]
    for ispos in np.arange(tmp.shape[0]):
        for imharm, mharm in enumerate(tmp[ispos]):
            dense_p3dz_t1[mharm,ispos] = orbp.p3dz[itime, imode, ispos, imharm]
    plt.pcolormesh(sfmin + deltas * dense_mmesh[0], dense_mmesh[1], np.abs(dense_p3dz_t1))
    plt.plot(sfmin + deltas * dense_mmesh[0][0,:], np.abs(p3m[imode]))
    plt.plot(sfmin + deltas * dense_mmesh[0][0,:], np.abs(p3m[imode])-mwidth)
    if qband:
        sgrid = orbp.orb5s.h5['equil/profiles/generic/sgrid_eq'][:]
        smask = (sgrid >= sfmin) * (sgrid <= sfmax)
        for sign in [-1,1]:
            qstyle = '-' if sign == 0 else '--'
            plt.plot(sgrid[smask], orbp.orb5s.h5['equil/profiles/generic/q'][smask]*ntor + sign*deltam, qstyle, lw=2, color='k')
            plt.plot(sgrid[smask], orbp.orb5s.h5['equil/profiles/generic/q'][smask]*ntor + sign*deltam, qstyle, lw=1, color='w')
    plt.gca().set_ylim(min([np.min(i) for i in orbp.mharms])-2,max([np.max(i) for i in orbp.mharms])+2)
    return plt.gcf(), plt.gca()

fig, ax = plot_dense(ntor=26, itime=-1, qband=True)

Data usage:¶

2D (nfreq_phipol):¶

* potsc = nchi * ns (allows us to get phi(m,s,t))
* potsp = nphi * ns (allows us to get phi(n,s,t) + frequency measurements for each toroidal mode)
* total = (nphi + nchi) * ns

new 3D (nfreq_3d && nsel_3d_diag = rhs_f):¶

pot3d = 2 * (nfilt2-nfilt1+1) * (2 * delta_m + 1) * (ns + nidbas)

old 3D (nfreq_3d && nsel_3d_diag = real):¶

phi = nphi * nchi * ns (1+moments)
  • both 3Ds are equivalent
  • both can be used to reconstruct 2D
  • both allow us to get phi(n,m,s,t)

Reductions:¶

3D new / 3D old = (2 * nmodes * (2*delta_m + 1)) / nphi * nchi
3D new / 2D = (2 * nmodes * (2*delta_m + 1)) / (nphi + nchi)

Example 1:¶

ns    = 512
nchi  = 256
nphi  = 128
deltam =  5
nfilt1 = 25
nfilt2 = 26
cubic splines

2D:
512*(256+128) = 196 608 data points per diagnostic step

new 3D:
2 * (2 modes) * (2 * 5 + 1) * (512+3) = 22 660 data points per diagnostic step

old 3D:
512 * 256 * 128 = 16 777 216 data points per diagnostic step (assuming no moments stored).

new / old 3D = 740x reduction
new 3D / 2D = 8.7x reduction

Example 2:¶

Same case, full radius:
q_max from ~1.25 to ~3.5
ns   ~ doubles
nchi ~ doubles
nphi   constant
2D     -> quadruples to   786432
new 3D -> doubles    to    45320
old 3D -> quadruples to 67108864
new / old 3D = ~1500

Largest example:¶

ns   ~ 1000
nchi ~ 1500
nphi ~  250
old 3D ~ 375M. Including moments data each 3D file ~10-60GB

Open issues:¶

  • 1D moments diagnostic previous done in nfreq_3d
  • Absolute normalizations*
  • spline coefficients -> radial coordinate*

*Noe's MATLAB script probably already corrects for these

Outlook¶

Alberto plans to add density(isp) & current(isp) options to new diagnostics.
(If needed): 3D new -> 3D old automatic conversion.

3D field data visualisation:¶

Does anyone currently use Visit/paraview/etc with the full 3D data? Are people interested in building 3D rendering workflows?
